* Expectation\nComponents
** Name
***_ Identifies the expectation
***_ Appears in monitoring dashboards
***_ Use descriptive names
***_ e.g. valid_customer_age
** Constraint
***_ SQL Boolean expression
***_ True = valid, False = violation
***_ Any valid SQL syntax
*** Limitations
****_ No custom Python functions
****_ No external service calls
****_ No subqueries
** Action
***_ Behavior on violation
***_ Warn, Drop, or Fail
** Example (Python)
***_ @dp.expect("name", "expression")
** Example (SQL)
***_ CONSTRAINT name EXPECT (expr)
@endmindmap
